00:22:26.199 --> 00:22:31.880
certified instructor come in, and just work on, you know, little projects with the team. So we had

00:22:31.880 --> 00:22:37.000
like a week long boot camp, or the team was not bothered by anyone, just to focus on learning.

00:22:37.800 --> 00:22:43.239
And then the third thing, and I think this is where it kind of closes the gap, is you can learn

00:22:43.239 --> 00:22:47.560
everything online, you can learn from instructors, but then when you have to apply it in the real

00:22:47.560 --> 00:22:53.319
world, it's not, you know, a one to one translation, real world data is not normally distributed, real

00:22:53.319 --> 00:22:59.640
world data has noise in it, you know, it doesn't work. So what we started doing is we started having

00:22:59.640 --> 00:23:05.800
monthly sessions. One, we started out with best practice sessions, where one of the team members

00:23:05.800 --> 00:23:11.800
would say, hey, look, this is a project I worked on, and here's how I approach the problem. So this

00:23:11.800 --> 00:23:16.599
helps someone that's new on the team, someone that's learning that software, to kind of get

00:23:16.599 --> 00:23:21.959
some exposure to it. The other thing we started doing more recently, is we said, you know what,

00:23:21.959 --> 00:23:26.680
we're kind of maxing out on our best practice sessions, we have nothing to share at some point.

